extracted_text: Density: Development may occur at a maximum density of two parcels per acre, provided all setbacks and all Beaufort County Health Department rules and regulations concerning placement and maintenance of septic tanks are observed. Mobile homes shall have a lot size of at least on acre. Development that occurs with utilization of a community sewer and water system may develop at a density of four parcels per acre.
llm_outputs.rationale: This section provides information about density requirements for the R-2 district, but does not explicitly state a minimum lot size. It mentions maximum densities of two parcels per acre or four parcels per acre with community sewer and water, but this is not equivalent to a minimum lot size.
